<CPU_SUPPORT WARNIG: The CPU in this host is not supported by
ESXi x.x.x. Please refer to the VMware Compatibility Guide (VCG)
for the list of supported CPUs.>

This error is the lessor of potential issues installing ESXi on a system that doesnt match comptability 
requirements. 

Most of the time these types of errors come from running or attemting to run/install the hypervisor on a 
personal home computer, that may be more than a few years old. 

If you are promoted with this error effect the following 

reboot into ESXi installer

You will see keyboard options that are present upon a 5 second countdown until installation is launched 

within the (5) seconds - press on your keyboard


///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

shift + O      


/://///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
///////////////That's the letter O as in oscar///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

AllowLegacyCPU=True


///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
///Make sure you do not backspace and there is at least one space between the default command that is present /////
//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

Press the Enter key & setup should continue as normal
